questiontext.text:
A fair 12-sided die (with sides numbered 1 through 12) will be rolled 289 times, and the sum (total) of those rolls will be recorded. What is the probability that the sum is less than 1933.5? P(∑X<1933.5)=?P\left(\sum X < 1933.5\right) = ?

To help you along, I will calculate the mean and standard deviation of single rolls. The formulas for an NN-sided die are can be derived from the formulas for discrete uniform distribution. $$\mu_{<span style="font-variant:small-caps;">X</span>} = \frac{N+1}{2} = \frac{12+1}{2} = 6.5 $$ $$\sigma_{<span style="font-variant:small-caps;">X</span>} = \sqrt{\frac{N^2-1}{12}} = \sqrt{\frac{12^2-1}{12}} = 3.4520525$$

Please use a normal approximation based on the central limit theorem.

generalfeedback.text:
We calculate the mean and standard deviation of the random sum using the formulas from the central limit theorem. $$\begin{aligned} \mu_{<span style="font-variant:small-caps;">\sum X</span>} &= n\mu_{<span style="font-variant:small-caps;">X</span>} \\ &= (289)(6.5) \\ &= 1878.5 \end{aligned}$$

$$\begin{aligned} \sigma_{<span style="font-variant:small-caps;">\sum X</span>} &= \sigma_{<span style="font-variant:small-caps;">X</span>} \sqrt{n} \\ &= (3.4520525)\sqrt{289} \\ &= 58.684893 \end{aligned}$$

The central limit theorem tells us that the random sum is approximately normal with the parameters calculated above.

∑X=N(1878.5,58.684893)\sum X = N(1878.5,\,58.684893)

In other words, we can approximate the summing of 289 rolls of 12-sided dice with a single spin of the following spinner.


Find the appropriate zz score.

$$z = \frac{(\sum x)-\mu_{<span style="font-variant:small-caps;">\sum X</span>}}{\sigma_{<span style="font-variant:small-caps;">\sum X</span>}} = \frac{1933.5-1878.5}{58.684893} = 0.9372088$$

You can round this to either 0.93 or 0.94. I will continue with the unrounded zz score. We now rephrase the question as a standard normal probability.

P(∑X<1933.5)=P(Z<0.9372088)P\left(\sum X < 1933.5\right) = P(Z<0.9372088) P(Z<0.9372088)=?P(Z<0.9372088) = ?

You can use the zz table to find the probability.

P(Z<0.9372088)=0.8256744P(Z<0.9372088) = 0.8256744

P(Z<0.93)=0.8238P(Z<0.93) = 0.8238 P(Z<0.94)=0.8264P(Z<0.94) = 0.8264
